sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant AuthGW as Kuadrant/Authorino<br/>Auth Gateway
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP pgx
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP RESP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>9090/TCP (obs)
    participant InfGW as Inference Gateway<br/>llm-d

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 1: File Upload
    Client->>AuthGW: POST /v1/files (multipart)<br/>Auth: API key / SA token
    AuthGW->>API: Forward + X-MaaS-Username header
    API->>S3: Upload JSONL file<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmed
    API->>PG: Insert file metadata<br/>Connection URL auth
    PG-->>API: File record created
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {file_id, status: "uploaded"}

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 2: Batch Job Submission
    Client->>AuthGW: POST /v1/batches<br/>Auth: API key / SA token
    AuthGW->>API: Forward + X-MaaS-Username header
    API->>PG: Insert batch metadata<br/>Connection URL auth
    PG-->>API: Batch record created
    API->>Redis: ZADD to priority queue<br/>Connection URL auth
    Redis-->>API: Enqueued
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {batch_id, status: "validating"}

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 3: Batch Job Processing
    Proc->>Redis: BZMPop (blocking dequeue)<br/>poll_interval: 5s
    Redis-->>Proc: Job ID + priority score
    Proc->>PG: Read batch metadata
    PG-->>Proc: Batch spec + input_file_id
    Proc->>S3: Download input JSONL file
    S3-->>Proc: File content
    Note over Proc: Preprocess: Build binary plan<br/>(sort by system prompt hash)

    loop For each request in plan (concurrency controlled)
        Proc->>InfGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token / mTLS
        InfGW-->>Proc: Inference response
        Proc->>Redis: Update progress counters
    end

    Proc->>S3: Upload output JSONL file<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>Proc: Upload confirmed
    Proc->>PG: Update batch status = completed
    Proc->>Redis: Set final progress status

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 4: Batch Cancellation
    Client->>AuthGW: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel
    AuthGW->>API: Forward + X-MaaS-Username header
    API->>Redis: RPush cancel event<br/>to event channel
    Redis-->>API: Event published
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: "cancelling"}
    Redis->>Proc: BLMPop cancel event
    Note over Proc: Cancel in-flight requests<br/>via context cancellation
    Proc->>PG: Update status = cancelled

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 5: Garbage Collection (periodic)
    Note over PG,S3: GC scans every 30 minutes
    activate PG
    Note right of PG: Query expired batches/files
    PG-->>S3: Delete expired physical files
    deactivate PG
